The biggest game this weekend in the Premier League, will be the London Derby between Arsenal and Chelsea. The Gunners have only won one out of their last 11 fixtures and are struggling to keep touch with the teams above them. On the other hand, Frank Lampard’s men have just won twice in their last seven games, losing 2-0 to Southampton in their last game. Kick off is 3pm West African time. Arsenal XI vs Chelsea: Leno, Maitland-Niles, Chambers, Luiz, Saka, Torreira, Guendouzi, Nelson, Ozil, Aubameyang, Lacazette Chelsea XI vs Arsenal: Kepa, Rudiger, Tomori, Zouma, Azpilicueta, Kante, Kovacic, Emerson, Willian, Mount, Abraham Sunday, December 29
